The paper discusses the use of deep neural networks generated using machine learning, which is a common topic in the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The focus on verifying the adversarial robustness of networks suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper's discussion of open questions and ongoing work suggests that it may also belong to the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), which often includes papers on ongoing research and future directions.
